18/09/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Gjorge Ivanov is expected to meet with the UN mediator in the name dispute between Macedonia and Greece, Matthew Nimetz, in New York, on the sidelines of the annual session of the UN General Assembly which opened this week, local media reported on Thursday (September 17th). 
No exact date for the meeting was mentioned. 
Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki has described the meeting as an opportunity for Macedonia to present its position in the row, which has hampered Skopje's European integration efforts. 
(Makfax, MRT, Makfax, Alsat - 17/09/09)
